<paragraph id="IAS36_22" base="SL32244" principles="no"><paranum>22</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IASÂ 36"/><data name="paranum" value="22"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS36_P0160"><xref base="SL148458" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0106">Recoverable amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0319"/></ph></xref> is determined for an individual asset, unless the asset does not generate cash inflows that are largely independent of those from other assets or groups of assets. If this is the case, recoverable amount is determined for the <xref base="SL148451" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0096">cash&#x2011;generating unit<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0031"/></ph></xref> to which the asset belongs (see <xref id="IAS36_X0220" base="A36-231" href="IAS36_65.dita#IAS36_65">paragraphs 65&#x2013;103</xref>), unless either: </p><ol id="IAS36_L0019" base="SL148517" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS36_P0161" base="SL148519">the asset&#x2019;s <xref base="SL148456" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0101">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> less costs of disposal is higher than its <xref base="SL148450" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0095">carrying amount<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0026"/></ph></xref>; or</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS36_P0162" base="SL148521">the asset&#x2019;s <xref base="SL148465" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0112">value in use<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0382"/></ph></xref> can be estimated to be close to its fair value less costs of disposal and <xref base="SL148456" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0101">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> less <xref base="SL148453" href="IAS36_6.dita#IAS36_6/IAS36_P0098">costs of disposal<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0058"/></ph></xref> can be measured.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>